---
description: Phaser scene and game object conventions
alwaysApply: false
globs: "**/*.{ts,js}"
---

When working in Phaser projects:

1. Keep scene classes focused — `preload` loads assets, `create` sets up objects, `update` handles per-frame logic only when needed.
2. Use typed scene classes (`extends Phaser.Scene`) and explicit `Scene` config keys.
3. Prefer scene events or a small game-state module over mutable globals.
4. Group related sprites with `Phaser.GameObjects.Group` or containers.
5. Register physics bodies in `create`; tune Arcade/Matter settings in scene or game config.
6. Clean up timers, tweens, and custom listeners in `shutdown` when scenes are restarted.
7. Match the repo's module style (ESM imports, path aliases) and bundler conventions.
